WEBVTT

00:00:00.100 --> 00:00:03.781
PulseProof is a trusted second screen for World Cup fans.

00:00:03.781 --> 00:00:07.461
It turns verified live match data into spoiler safe Catch

00:00:07.461 --> 00:00:11.142
Up, match communities and a non transferable fan identity on

00:00:11.142 --> 00:00:14.823
chain. The journey starts before kickoff, continues during play and

00:00:14.823 --> 00:00:17.031
remains useful after the final whistle.

00:00:18.100 --> 00:00:22.567
TxLINE is the primary live signal. PulseProof normalizes activated devnet

00:00:22.567 --> 00:00:27.034
fixtures and events into a public Server Sent Events stream.

00:00:27.034 --> 00:00:31.500
The Live Center keeps World Cup competition labels, official team

00:00:31.500 --> 00:00:35.967
abbreviations, flags, live status, finished results, upcoming fixtures, stadiums and

00:00:35.967 --> 00:00:39.987
kickoff times in one view with clear source labels.

00:00:41.100 --> 00:00:44.862
Here is the complete replay test, not a static score.

00:00:44.862 --> 00:00:48.625
We press Start Catch Up and the player advances from

00:00:48.625 --> 00:00:52.387
Event one through nine using the same scoreboard, momentum and

00:00:52.387 --> 00:00:56.150
timeline as live coverage. Pause, resume and one, two or

00:00:56.150 --> 00:00:59.912
four times speed remain interactive. The final TxLINE snapshot supplies

00:00:59.912 --> 00:01:03.675
nine verified on pitch moments when the historical endpoint is

00:01:03.675 --> 00:01:07.437
empty. We then inspect the full time score, Match brief,

00:01:07.437 --> 00:01:11.200
Jude Bellingham's goal, Trevoh Chalobah's substitution, created chances and both

00:01:11.200 --> 00:01:13.457
VAR reviews with source sequence numbers.

00:01:17.100 --> 00:01:20.661
Phantom stays connected while the user moves from Live Center

00:01:20.661 --> 00:01:24.221
to Fan Zone. The profile belongs to the wallet, so

00:01:24.221 --> 00:01:27.782
the display name, points, streak and inventory follow without a

00:01:27.782 --> 00:01:28.494
second connection.

00:01:29.100 --> 00:01:32.501
Profile editing creates a readable alias for match chat. The

00:01:32.501 --> 00:01:35.902
new name is prepared on the Fan Alias account on

00:01:35.902 --> 00:01:39.303
chain. It is not stored as a temporary browser preference.

00:01:40.100 --> 00:01:44.228
Phantom shows the real devnet transaction. After approval, the page

00:01:44.228 --> 00:01:48.356
updates immediately to Cryptovuive twenty six. It displays a confirmed

00:01:48.356 --> 00:01:52.485
receipt and Explorer link, then keeps the new alias after

00:01:52.485 --> 00:01:52.897
reload.

00:01:55.100 --> 00:01:58.797
Daily check in uses Solana time. The interface previews seven

00:01:58.797 --> 00:02:02.493
streak days and disables duplicate claims within the same UTC

00:02:02.493 --> 00:02:02.863
day.

00:02:05.100 --> 00:02:08.762
One Phantom approval creates the check in proof. The page

00:02:08.762 --> 00:02:12.423
immediately marks today complete, raises the streak and points, and

00:02:12.423 --> 00:02:15.353
shows a confirmed devnet receipt without any reload.

00:02:18.100 --> 00:02:21.908
The daily quiz draws five questions from ten thousand deterministic

00:02:21.908 --> 00:02:25.716
World Cup variations built from sourced facts. Answer links stay

00:02:25.716 --> 00:02:29.525
hidden and explanations appear only after selection. This run scores

00:02:29.525 --> 00:02:33.333
five out of five. Daily rewards are single use, while

00:02:33.333 --> 00:02:36.379
practice rounds remain unlimited and provide no rewards.

00:02:46.100 --> 00:02:50.457
Phantom signs the authorized points claim. Seventy points arrive immediately,

00:02:50.457 --> 00:02:54.814
the button changes to Claimed today, and the transaction receipt

00:02:54.814 --> 00:02:56.992
remains independently verifiable on Explorer.

00:02:59.100 --> 00:03:02.922
The reward catalog contains thirty six original and non transferable

00:03:02.922 --> 00:03:06.744
medals, badges, avatar frames and characters. Limited editions always show

00:03:06.744 --> 00:03:10.566
a clear closing date. We scroll through every item before

00:03:10.566 --> 00:03:14.387
randomly selecting Bolt Keeper. Prices are fixed by the catalog

00:03:14.387 --> 00:03:18.209
on chain, so the client cannot invent a cheaper redemption.

00:03:27.100 --> 00:03:31.025
The transaction completes atomically: Bolt Keeper becomes owned and active,

00:03:31.025 --> 00:03:34.558
and the balance drops by one hundred sixty points.

00:03:37.100 --> 00:03:41.042
Chat belongs to each match, beside the live or replay

00:03:41.042 --> 00:03:44.984
timeline. The composer uses the alias stored on chain and

00:03:44.984 --> 00:03:48.137
blocks links, betting, wallet secrets and anonymous impersonation.

00:03:49.100 --> 00:03:53.277
Posting requires a fresh Phantom message signature, not a fee.

00:03:53.277 --> 00:03:57.455
After approval, the server verifies the wallet, alias, fixture and

00:03:57.455 --> 00:04:01.632
replay protection value. The signed message appears instantly as Cryptovuive

00:04:01.632 --> 00:04:04.974
twenty six in the England and Argentina room.

00:04:07.100 --> 00:04:11.488
Finally, Judge Room runs the product instead of trusting slides.

00:04:11.488 --> 00:04:15.876
Eight fresh checks validate production identity, the World Cup catalog,

00:04:15.876 --> 00:04:20.264
public SSE, spoiler isolation, a signed Catch Up Capsule, Ed25519

00:04:20.264 --> 00:04:24.651
verification inside the browser, the live Solana programs and the

00:04:24.651 --> 00:04:29.039
offline cache boundary. This run passes eight of eight and

00:04:29.039 --> 00:04:33.427
exposes current points, alias, finalized quiz and reward receipts, Explorer,

00:04:33.427 --> 00:04:35.621
CI and the public repository.

00:04:39.100 --> 00:04:43.426
PulseProof turns live context into community identity and verifiable memory.

00:04:43.426 --> 00:04:47.752
Before, during and after the match, every match leaves a

00:04:47.752 --> 00:04:48.185
memory.

